From: nvukobratTT <nvukobrat@tenstorrent.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Add TTNNCheckDRAMBudget pre-flight pass to catch OOM before execution

Adds a new MLIR pass `ttnn-check-dram-budget` that runs after
`ttnn-deallocate` and simulates tensor lifetimes to estimate peak DRAM
usage per chip. If the estimate exceeds the device's usable DRAM
budget, the pass emits a compile-time error with an actionable message
instead of letting the program reach execution and hang silently (GH #11).

For TP-sharded models (SPMD), tensor shapes in the IR already reflect
per-chip sizes after the SPMD sharding pass, so the check compares
against the single-chip DRAM budget directly.

The pass also emits a warning at 90% utilisation to provide an early
signal before the threshold is crossed.

Fixes: https://github.com/nvukobratTT/tt-xla/issues/11 (Solution 3)
